1
00:00:01,376 --> 00:00:04,254
[theme music playing]

2
00:01:24,763 --> 00:01:26,348
[imitates car revving]

3
00:01:26,514 --> 00:01:29,100
Near, if you don't mind me asking,
what do you make of all this?

4
00:01:29,184 --> 00:01:31,686
I'm interested to hear
what your thoughts are on this case.

5
00:01:32,103 --> 00:01:34,689
[Near] The current Kira is foolish
and overconfident,

6
00:01:34,773 --> 00:01:37,692
not to mention unusually cooperative
with the task force.

7
00:01:38,485 --> 00:01:40,987
So much so, that I suspect
he's working hand in hand with them.

8
00:01:41,655 --> 00:01:43,615
-You think so?
-That would make the second L and Kira...

9
00:01:44,866 --> 00:01:46,284
one in the same person.

10
00:01:46,576 --> 00:01:47,452
[Rester] What?

11
00:01:48,370 --> 00:01:51,581
-That can't be. Are you serious?
-[Near] Yes, I am.

12
00:01:51,956 --> 00:01:55,126
Having said that, I'll admit that
I'm only seven percent certain.

13
00:01:56,628 --> 00:01:58,046
[Near] Don't worry, Commander Rester,

14
00:01:58,254 --> 00:02:00,924
making assumptions
is part of any investigation.

15
00:02:01,508 --> 00:02:03,927
If we're wrong,
all it'll cost is an apology.

16
00:02:04,124 --> 00:02:07,044
JUSTICE

17
00:02:10,725 --> 00:02:14,521
[child] There have been less crimes lately
in Japan and around the world.

18
00:02:14,729 --> 00:02:16,147
It's because of Kira.

19
00:02:16,356 --> 00:02:19,067
My daddy told me
that if you do something bad,

20
00:02:19,150 --> 00:02:20,402
your name will be written
on the Internet...

21
00:02:20,485 --> 00:02:22,237
-Your name, please.
-...and Kira will kill you.

22
00:02:22,445 --> 00:02:23,738
Come on, I don't have all day.

23
00:02:23,822 --> 00:02:25,990
How am I supposed to file this report
without your name?

24
00:02:26,157 --> 00:02:28,576
Give me a break. Please, not my name!

25
00:02:29,744 --> 00:02:32,497
Leave me alone or I'll put your names
on the Internet!

26
00:02:32,653 --> 00:02:34,457
KIRA, PLEASE KILL...

27
00:02:46,386 --> 00:02:50,014
[tap dripping]

28
00:02:59,441 --> 00:03:01,609
[man on radio] I will proclaim this
right here and now,

29
00:03:01,693 --> 00:03:04,821
to all the people of the Earth,
Kira is true justice!

30
00:03:04,946 --> 00:03:06,865
[jingle playing]

31
00:03:06,948 --> 00:03:09,200
KIRA'S KINGDOM

32
00:03:11,119 --> 00:03:14,914
Good evening. It is my honor
to be appointed by Kira as his spokesman.

33
00:03:15,081 --> 00:03:17,459
This is not a hoax.
It's the absolute truth.

34
00:03:17,834 --> 00:03:21,671
I realize that there will be many people
who might try to have me killed now,

35
00:03:22,130 --> 00:03:24,716
but I am prepared to risk my life
in order to spread Kira's vision.

36
00:03:24,799 --> 00:03:26,134
NEW JAPANESE TASK FORCE HEADQUARTERS

37
00:03:26,217 --> 00:03:28,219
[Aizawa] Kira's Kingdom, huh?
What a horrible title.

38
00:03:28,303 --> 00:03:29,763
[Ide] This is insanity.

39
00:03:30,847 --> 00:03:34,017
Trying to capture Kira
is an unforgivable crime.

40
00:03:34,350 --> 00:03:37,145
-If you happen to know anybody...
-If anybody deserves to be killed by Kira,

41
00:03:37,228 --> 00:03:38,313
it's this guy.

42
00:03:38,396 --> 00:03:40,523
-...a criminal or a regular citizen...
-Oh.

43
00:03:40,690 --> 00:03:42,484
Switch it back to the press conference.

44
00:03:42,567 --> 00:03:44,569
-The president's about to start.
-[audience applauding on TV]

45
00:03:44,986 --> 00:03:47,238
-[camera shutters clicking]
-[Matusda] I wonder what it's about?

46
00:03:47,322 --> 00:03:50,700
All they said was that it was gonna be
some sort of international announcement.

47
00:03:51,075 --> 00:03:53,077
You don't do anything but watch TV,
do you?

48
00:03:53,203 --> 00:03:54,537
Uh, what? [grunts]

49
00:03:55,705 --> 00:03:58,541
Good morning,
I'm gonna try to keep this brief.

50
00:04:01,169 --> 00:04:03,213
-Huh?
-[Light] No way!

51
00:04:03,588 --> 00:04:08,384
[sighs] The United States
will no longer oppose Kira.

52
00:04:08,551 --> 00:04:11,554
-[all gasp]
-[audience yelling indistinctly on TV]

53
00:04:11,805 --> 00:04:14,140
[grunts] Those cowards!

54
00:04:14,724 --> 00:04:18,686
[Light] I've done it! I've even brought
America to its knees.

55
00:04:18,812 --> 00:04:21,147
Huh? What the hell is he talking about?

56
00:04:21,481 --> 00:04:22,899
Have they been threatened or something?

57
00:04:23,024 --> 00:04:25,610
Are you saying that Kira is justice?

58
00:04:25,693 --> 00:04:28,321
[indistinct yelling]

59
00:04:28,780 --> 00:04:31,783
Justice? No, no, I never said that.

60
00:04:31,908 --> 00:04:34,911
But because of Kira, war and conflict
have ceased to exist.

61
00:04:35,036 --> 00:04:37,413
Criminal organizations
are in a state of ruin,

62
00:04:37,539 --> 00:04:40,542
not only in the United States,
but in all free nations.

63
00:04:40,708 --> 00:04:44,379
Anyone who defies Kira head on
will be killed. That is a fact.

64
00:04:44,546 --> 00:04:46,840
We are not acknowledging Kira
as a symbol of justice,

65
00:04:47,006 --> 00:04:51,553
we are simply saying that, as a country,
we will not take any actions against him.

66
00:04:51,636 --> 00:04:53,263
[man 1 on TV] How is that any different?

67
00:04:53,388 --> 00:04:56,724
[man 2 on TV] You're saying
that you accept Kira? Explain yourself!

68
00:04:56,891 --> 00:04:59,352
[man 3 on TV ] And you call yourself
the representative of our country?

69
00:04:59,477 --> 00:05:01,771
I can't believe it. This is America!

70
00:05:01,938 --> 00:05:04,357
How can their government do something
so cowardly like this?

71
00:05:04,983 --> 00:05:07,735
Uh… do you guys mind if I ask
a serious question?

72
00:05:07,902 --> 00:05:09,737
Oh, boy, what is it this time?

73
00:05:09,863 --> 00:05:11,489
Are you telling us you're not
always serious?

74
00:05:12,490 --> 00:05:15,493
Do you guys ever think that maybe
Kira isn't completely evil?

75
00:05:15,910 --> 00:05:18,580
-What?
-What kind of question is that, Matsuda?

76
00:05:18,705 --> 00:05:22,625
I've been thinking about it and part of me
just doesn't believe that he is.

77
00:05:23,167 --> 00:05:25,795
So now you think Kira is justice too?

78
00:05:26,337 --> 00:05:27,589
I don't really know.

79
00:05:28,256 --> 00:05:32,135
But I think that Kira's trying to fight
evil and change the world in his own way.

80
00:05:32,302 --> 00:05:36,014
And well, the world's become a good place
for people who live honest lives,

81
00:05:36,139 --> 00:05:38,391
-so, maybe--
-You're wrong, Matsuda.

82
00:05:38,516 --> 00:05:41,185
People are only afraid
of losing their own lives.

83
00:05:41,436 --> 00:05:42,687
How can you think that's real peace?

84
00:05:43,021 --> 00:05:45,982
I understand that! Believe me,
I know that as well as you.

85
00:05:46,149 --> 00:05:48,318
It's just that I can also understand
the other side.

86
00:05:48,401 --> 00:05:51,070
I can see why all those people
call Kira a savior.

87
00:05:51,237 --> 00:05:52,280
I'm not like you.

88
00:05:52,655 --> 00:05:55,700
[Matsuda] When it comes down it,
I've always been a really weak person.

89
00:05:55,909 --> 00:05:59,162
But I'm also a detective.
I can't accept Kira.

90
00:05:59,412 --> 00:06:03,625
I know it's my duty to catch him.
No, I want to catch him.

91
00:06:03,708 --> 00:06:06,002
It's just that I can't completely
hate him either.

92
00:06:06,377 --> 00:06:09,589
I guess I must be crazy or something, huh?

93
00:06:09,964 --> 00:06:12,508
[sighs] No, you're not crazy.
You're normal.

94
00:06:12,759 --> 00:06:13,635
[all] Huh?

95
00:06:13,843 --> 00:06:16,012
You too, Light?
What are you talking about?

96
00:06:16,721 --> 00:06:20,016
[Light] I'm sure that on some level,
Kira probably knows

97
00:06:20,141 --> 00:06:21,851
-that what he's doing is evil.
-[Ryuk cackles]

98
00:06:22,185 --> 00:06:26,356
But he'll try to change the world
even as a martyr, at the cost of his soul.

99
00:06:26,731 --> 00:06:28,566
That's his brand of justice.

100
00:06:29,275 --> 00:06:31,486
I bet that's what's going
through Kira's mind.

101
00:06:32,403 --> 00:06:36,866
Anyway, we shouldn't be arguing about it.
Good or evil, it's not our call.

102
00:06:37,283 --> 00:06:39,285
All we have to think about
is catching him.

103
00:06:40,328 --> 00:06:42,914
If Kira gets caught,
then that makes him evil.

104
00:06:43,122 --> 00:06:45,500
But if he wins and rules the world,
then I guess he's justice.

105
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:46,960
Hmm...

106
00:06:50,254 --> 00:06:54,258
[Light] But from now on, the world
will start leaning in favor of Kira.

107
00:06:54,467 --> 00:06:59,305
It's only a matter of time.
Kira will be justice.

108
00:07:01,099 --> 00:07:02,725
[Gevanni]
What's going to happen to us now?

109
00:07:03,142 --> 00:07:06,729
[Near] It looks like we've been disbanded
thanks to that chicken of a president.

110
00:07:07,146 --> 00:07:11,401
No, he's not even a chicken.
He's less than a maggot.

111
00:07:14,445 --> 00:07:16,030
[Near] You've got to be kidding.

112
00:07:16,197 --> 00:07:19,075
There's no way accepting Kira
will lead to anything good.

113
00:07:23,454 --> 00:07:24,872
[shower water splashing]

114
00:07:40,972 --> 00:07:41,931
Huh?

115
00:07:45,852 --> 00:07:46,728
[gasps]

116
00:07:48,980 --> 00:07:50,231
So you're alive?

117
00:07:53,901 --> 00:07:54,819
Near!

118
00:07:55,403 --> 00:07:56,279
Huh?

119
00:07:59,323 --> 00:08:01,576
-What should we do?
-Let him in.

120
00:08:01,701 --> 00:08:02,952
[beeping]

121
00:08:12,795 --> 00:08:14,297
Mello, welcome.

122
00:08:14,464 --> 00:08:15,631
Drop your weapon!

123
00:08:15,923 --> 00:08:16,883
[Mello snarls]

124
00:08:20,845 --> 00:08:23,389
[Near] Everyone, please put away
your guns.

125
00:08:23,723 --> 00:08:25,892
Having a shoot-out here
would achieve nothing.

126
00:08:26,768 --> 00:08:30,063
Sir, with all due respect,
Mello's the one who killed our partners.

127
00:08:30,313 --> 00:08:32,065
[Near] Please don't make me
say it again.

128
00:08:32,482 --> 00:08:35,610
Remember that our primary objective
is still to catch Kira.

129
00:08:35,777 --> 00:08:39,030
Killing Mello right now will do nothing
to benefit our investigation.

130
00:08:39,530 --> 00:08:40,406
Hmm...

131
00:08:41,616 --> 00:08:42,492
Alright.

132
00:08:45,286 --> 00:08:48,706
It seems like things have been going
just as you planned, Near.

133
00:08:48,915 --> 00:08:52,043
[Near] Yes. I take it you've already
heard all about the second L

134
00:08:52,126 --> 00:08:53,169
from Lidner by now?

135
00:08:53,461 --> 00:08:56,589
I've pretty much figured out who Kira is
and it's mostly thanks

136
00:08:56,672 --> 00:08:58,257
-to everything you've done.
-[Mello growling]

137
00:08:58,966 --> 00:09:01,761
[cocking gun] Shut up, Near!

138
00:09:03,054 --> 00:09:06,182
I'm not just a tool for you to use
in order to solve your puzzles, y'know?

139
00:09:07,350 --> 00:09:10,686
Mello, if you really wanna shoot me
then go ahead and do it.

140
00:09:15,900 --> 00:09:18,820
Stop! If you shoot him,
then the rest of us will have no choice

141
00:09:18,945 --> 00:09:22,115
but to shoot you too.
What will it solve if both of you die?

142
00:09:22,782 --> 00:09:24,075
That's just what Kira wants.

143
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,159
[grunts]

144
00:09:27,829 --> 00:09:29,080
You have a good point.

145
00:09:29,288 --> 00:09:31,124
Anyway, I'm only here for one thing.

146
00:09:31,207 --> 00:09:33,417
I came to take back
that photograph you have.

147
00:09:33,501 --> 00:09:36,003
[Near] Of course.
I got it from the orphanage.

148
00:09:36,087 --> 00:09:38,131
There was only one
and no copies have been made.

149
00:09:38,714 --> 00:09:41,384
I've already gone ahead and dealt
with everyone who knows your face,

150
00:09:41,509 --> 00:09:44,387
both inside and outside Wammy's house.
They'll keep quiet.

151
00:09:45,304 --> 00:09:47,348
I can't say a hundred percent for certain,

152
00:09:47,431 --> 00:09:50,476
but it shouldn't be possible
for you to be killed by the notebook.

153
00:09:52,228 --> 00:09:55,106
[Near] Is that the only business
you had with me, Mello?

154
00:09:57,692 --> 00:09:59,569
[sighs] Near…

155
00:10:01,445 --> 00:10:04,824
[bells chiming]

156
00:10:09,912 --> 00:10:11,539
[Mello] Let's get one thing straight.

157
00:10:11,747 --> 00:10:14,625
I have no intention of working together
with you on this.

158
00:10:14,709 --> 00:10:15,793
[Near] Yes, I know.

159
00:10:16,210 --> 00:10:18,796
At the same time, I can't just take
my photo and leave.

160
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:20,798
That wouldn't be right.
So I'll settle my debt.

161
00:10:20,923 --> 00:10:21,966
[Near] Hmm?

162
00:10:22,717 --> 00:10:26,012
[Mello] The killer notebook...
it belongs to a Shinigami.

163
00:10:26,262 --> 00:10:29,098
Whoever touches it
is able to see a god of death.

164
00:10:30,391 --> 00:10:31,309
That's crazy.

165
00:10:31,392 --> 00:10:33,311
Who the hell would believe
in something like that?

166
00:10:33,436 --> 00:10:35,855
[Near] I would. I believe him completely.

167
00:10:35,980 --> 00:10:38,691
What good would it do for him
to tell an outrageous lie like that?

168
00:10:38,774 --> 00:10:41,068
Even if he had something to gain,
he could at least come up

169
00:10:41,152 --> 00:10:46,073
with a more believable story.
Therefore, these gods of death must exist.

170
00:10:46,157 --> 00:10:49,535
The notebook I obtained had previously
belonged to another Shinigami.

171
00:10:49,619 --> 00:10:51,037
Perhaps even Kira himself.

172
00:10:51,287 --> 00:10:54,874
Also, some of the rules written inside
are actually fake.

173
00:10:55,499 --> 00:10:57,501
That's all I can tell you for now.

174
00:11:10,348 --> 00:11:12,475
-Near?
-Mello?

175
00:11:17,688 --> 00:11:20,233
Which of us is gonna reach Kira first,
I wonder?

176
00:11:21,067 --> 00:11:22,568
The race is on.

177
00:11:23,236 --> 00:11:25,780
[Mello] We're both headed
towards the same destination.

178
00:11:26,030 --> 00:11:27,531
I'll be waiting for you.

179
00:11:28,115 --> 00:11:29,492
[Near scoffs] Right.

180
00:12:00,314 --> 00:12:01,357
[Near] Fake rules...

181
00:12:01,941 --> 00:12:04,527
There's no doubt that the notebook
can cause heart attacks

182
00:12:04,610 --> 00:12:06,529
and control its victims to a degree.

183
00:12:07,071 --> 00:12:10,366
As for burning it or tearing it up,
the notebook still exists

184
00:12:10,491 --> 00:12:13,202
and there's no way to confirm
the rule one way or the other.

185
00:12:13,744 --> 00:12:15,079
That means...

186
00:12:22,044 --> 00:12:24,880
The false rule must be the one
that states a person will die

187
00:12:24,964 --> 00:12:27,550
if he doesn't write a name
within 13 days.

188
00:12:31,345 --> 00:12:32,680
-[Near] Gevanni.
-Huh?

189
00:12:32,805 --> 00:12:34,515
[Near] Please set up a connection to L.

190
00:12:34,724 --> 00:12:37,059
-Yes, sir.
-[keyboard clicking]

191
00:12:37,476 --> 00:12:39,228
-[beeping]
-[Matusda] It's Near.

192
00:12:40,521 --> 00:12:41,397
Yes?

193
00:12:41,897 --> 00:12:43,941
[Near] L, I thought you should know
that we caught Mello.

194
00:12:44,025 --> 00:12:46,444
-[all gasping]
-But he escaped soon afterwards.

195
00:12:46,777 --> 00:12:47,653
[all sighing]

196
00:12:47,737 --> 00:12:50,197
[Near] We were able
to interrogate him for a while.

197
00:12:50,781 --> 00:12:54,201
He didn't really escape, did he?
You let him get away. Am I right?

198
00:12:54,327 --> 00:12:57,246
No, we tried to restrain him
but he was too quick.

199
00:12:57,455 --> 00:13:00,207
Anyway, Mello mentioned
that there was some sort of Shinigami

200
00:13:00,291 --> 00:13:01,834
-attached to the notebook.
-[gasps softly]

201
00:13:02,209 --> 00:13:05,254
[Near] Have you been able to confirm
the existence of such a creature?

202
00:13:05,921 --> 00:13:09,508
Yes. I can tell you for a fact
that Shinigami do exist.

203
00:13:09,592 --> 00:13:11,677
I didn't share that information
with you in the beginning

204
00:13:11,761 --> 00:13:13,721
because I was certain
you would never believe me.

205
00:13:14,305 --> 00:13:17,475
[Near] I would like to ask the Shinigami
a few questions.

206
00:13:17,767 --> 00:13:19,518
Forget it, I'm not up for that.

207
00:13:19,852 --> 00:13:21,979
The thing that's bothering me
the most about this

208
00:13:22,104 --> 00:13:24,482
is the issue of those rules
written in the notebook.

209
00:13:24,607 --> 00:13:26,650
I have reason to believe
that one of them is fake.

210
00:13:26,776 --> 00:13:29,028
-[all] Huh?
-[Light] A fake rule?

211
00:13:29,111 --> 00:13:32,990
[Near] Yes. L, I'd be interested
to hear your thoughts on this.

212
00:13:33,157 --> 00:13:35,659
Out of all the rules,
which do you think is the fake?

213
00:13:35,743 --> 00:13:37,787
-I'd like to know.
-[sighs]

214
00:13:38,871 --> 00:13:41,540
By process of elimination,
the obvious choice

215
00:13:41,665 --> 00:13:44,085
would be the one stating
that the owner of the notebook will die

216
00:13:44,168 --> 00:13:46,379
if they don't write a new name in it
every 13 days.

217
00:13:46,462 --> 00:13:47,671
I don't believe that.

218
00:13:47,963 --> 00:13:51,175
[Near] I thought you might say so.
I've reached the same conclusion.

219
00:13:53,636 --> 00:13:56,931
Hmm. Shinigami, you know the rules
of the notebook well.

220
00:13:57,181 --> 00:13:58,849
Tell us. Are any of them false?

221
00:13:59,058 --> 00:14:01,060
No, they are all real.

222
00:14:02,436 --> 00:14:05,272
[Near] I see. You have a Shinigami
there with you?

223
00:14:05,481 --> 00:14:06,357
Yes.

224
00:14:07,024 --> 00:14:08,317
[Near] Is that so?

225
00:14:09,068 --> 00:14:11,445
I think I'm beginning to get the picture.

226
00:14:11,654 --> 00:14:13,823
In other words, Kira is there in the room

227
00:14:13,906 --> 00:14:16,909
and he's making the Shinigami lie
on his behalf.

228
00:14:17,118 --> 00:14:20,079
[Ryuk] Whoa, this guy's good.
He nailed it.

229
00:14:20,830 --> 00:14:22,039
I don't get what he means.

230
00:14:22,164 --> 00:14:24,333
So what if the Shinigami's lying
and the rule's fake?

231
00:14:24,458 --> 00:14:26,377
It doesn't really change anything,
does it?

232
00:14:26,585 --> 00:14:27,586
[Aizawa] Yes, it does.

233
00:14:27,670 --> 00:14:29,839
It means that Light's incarceration
would be meaningless.

234
00:14:30,339 --> 00:14:32,967
The rule says you die
if you don't continue writing names,

235
00:14:33,134 --> 00:14:36,929
but if that's false, being alive
after 13 days in confinement

236
00:14:37,054 --> 00:14:38,431
wouldn't really prove anything.

237
00:14:40,141 --> 00:14:42,726
But even if that's true,
it doesn't mean he's guilty!

238
00:14:42,810 --> 00:14:44,895
Besides, there's no way
that Light could be Kira.

239
00:14:45,020 --> 00:14:47,314
Before he passed away,
the Deputy Director himself

240
00:14:47,398 --> 00:14:49,525
was able to confirm
that he didn't have a notebook.

241
00:14:58,284 --> 00:15:01,203
[Near] If there's a problem,
I suggest we verify the rule this way.

242
00:15:01,662 --> 00:15:04,540
I will volunteer to write down
Mello's real name in the notebook.

243
00:15:04,665 --> 00:15:05,666
[all gasp]

244
00:15:05,791 --> 00:15:09,545
[Near] Of course, that means he'll die.
If I also die 13 days later,

245
00:15:09,670 --> 00:15:11,213
well, then I guess Kira wins.

246
00:15:11,589 --> 00:15:13,924
Either way, it's a gamble
I'm quite willing to make.

247
00:15:14,049 --> 00:15:16,719
What? So this is just a game to him?

248
00:15:17,303 --> 00:15:19,430
[Near]
Testing and confirming the 13-day rule

249
00:15:19,513 --> 00:15:23,142
can only benefit the Kira investigation.
And other than my possible death,

250
00:15:23,225 --> 00:15:24,518
there would be no drawbacks.

251
00:15:24,935 --> 00:15:27,813
I'm willing to put my life on the line
if it will help us solve the case.

252
00:15:27,938 --> 00:15:30,733
[Light] If I answer him based
on my feelings alone,

253
00:15:30,858 --> 00:15:32,860
it'll only make me look worse to everyone.

254
00:15:32,985 --> 00:15:36,614
Could you please wait for a moment?
We need to discuss your suggestion.

255
00:15:36,739 --> 00:15:37,990
[microphone switch clicks]

256
00:15:38,157 --> 00:15:40,201
Okay. What are your thoughts?

257
00:15:40,826 --> 00:15:45,331
We can say that we must respect
human life and deny this request...

258
00:15:45,748 --> 00:15:47,291
but I can't suggest that.

259
00:15:47,958 --> 00:15:49,710
I'm the one under suspicion.

260
00:15:50,169 --> 00:15:53,047
It's a tough call.
Mello killed the Deputy Director.

261
00:15:53,214 --> 00:15:55,090
If Near is willing, I wouldn't stop him.

262
00:15:55,466 --> 00:15:57,176
I'm against the idea, myself.

263
00:15:57,384 --> 00:15:59,929
I don't believe that Kira's hiding
among us.

264
00:16:00,346 --> 00:16:03,098
We can't use the notebook,
no matter what happens.

265
00:16:03,390 --> 00:16:06,685
We should respect
the Deputy Director's wishes to the end.

266
00:16:06,769 --> 00:16:08,854
I feel the same. I'm opposed to the test.

267
00:16:09,271 --> 00:16:10,189
[Light] Mm.

268
00:16:12,024 --> 00:16:14,109
Near, we've talked it over
and we can't allow you

269
00:16:14,193 --> 00:16:15,528
to use the notebook like that.

270
00:16:15,903 --> 00:16:18,447
[Near] I had a feeling you might say so.
No matter.

271
00:16:18,697 --> 00:16:20,699
Just one last question before I go.

272
00:16:21,075 --> 00:16:23,536
To the members
of the Japanese Task Force...

273
00:16:23,953 --> 00:16:25,871
Was there ever a point
in the investigation

274
00:16:26,038 --> 00:16:28,082
where the second L was suspected
to be Kira,

275
00:16:28,165 --> 00:16:30,000
even if the suspicions were later dropped?

276
00:16:30,584 --> 00:16:33,254
If you've been listening
to our conversation so far

277
00:16:33,337 --> 00:16:36,507
and have any intention of helping
my investigation and taking down Kira,

278
00:16:36,924 --> 00:16:38,842
then call the number
I'm about to give you.

279
00:16:39,009 --> 00:16:42,388
Day or night, I will answer.
The choice is up to you.

280
00:16:43,430 --> 00:16:45,849
[Aizawa] There's no way
that Light could be Kira.

281
00:16:46,016 --> 00:16:48,769
No, it's more like
I don't wanna believe he's Kira.

282
00:16:48,852 --> 00:16:51,730
But if the 13-day rule is fake,

283
00:16:51,855 --> 00:16:54,483
then we really can't say for sure
that he's innocent.

284
00:16:54,900 --> 00:16:56,944
This could change everything.

285
00:16:57,945 --> 00:16:59,196
[cackling]

286
00:17:01,532 --> 00:17:04,618
[Light] Near. I have to kill him!

287
00:17:07,997 --> 00:17:10,958
[phone ringing]

288
00:17:12,543 --> 00:17:15,337
-Yes, hello?
-[automated Kira voice] This is Kira.

289
00:17:15,963 --> 00:17:17,381
Is this a joke?

290
00:17:17,506 --> 00:17:19,592
[Kira] If you want proof,
I can read out a list of people

291
00:17:19,675 --> 00:17:21,302
that I'm going to punish tomorrow.

292
00:17:21,427 --> 00:17:24,513
That way, you can check it
and make your final decision afterwards.

293
00:17:25,222 --> 00:17:28,475
Mr. President, I am very grateful
that you and your country

294
00:17:28,559 --> 00:17:32,605
have sympathized with me, but I'm afraid
even that much isn't enough.

295
00:17:32,855 --> 00:17:36,650
The SPK is still trying to catch me
despite your recent announcement.

296
00:17:36,942 --> 00:17:41,155
I want you to stop them immediately,
and formally disband them.

297
00:17:42,698 --> 00:17:48,203
At the same time, I want you to use
the American police, the CIA, the FBI,

298
00:17:48,329 --> 00:17:51,332
and all other law enforcement
organizations at your disposal

299
00:17:51,457 --> 00:17:54,418
to find out where the SPK members
are currently hiding.

300
00:17:54,543 --> 00:17:56,837
As soon as you've found
their base of operations,

301
00:17:56,920 --> 00:17:59,506
I want you to forward that information
to a third party.

302
00:17:59,590 --> 00:18:01,800
I will give you this contact shortly.

303
00:18:02,468 --> 00:18:06,847
Mr. President, whether you live
a long life or not is up to you.

304
00:18:07,097 --> 00:18:08,641
Don't forget that.

305
00:18:09,475 --> 00:18:10,851
I understand.

306
00:18:11,101 --> 00:18:12,394
[hangs up]

307
00:18:15,189 --> 00:18:16,315
[President groans]

308
00:18:17,399 --> 00:18:19,902
-[man 1] Mr. Demegawa! Please wait!
-[man 2] Why are you going to New York?

309
00:18:19,985 --> 00:18:23,822
[Demegawa] We are going to crush
an organization that dares to defy Kira.

310
00:18:24,031 --> 00:18:25,616
It'll be on live TV.

311
00:18:26,992 --> 00:18:29,078
This is a direct order from Kira,

312
00:18:29,161 --> 00:18:31,413
and it came through the President
of the United States himself.

313
00:18:31,497 --> 00:18:32,373
[all] Huh?

314
00:18:32,665 --> 00:18:34,625
I don't know what's gonna happen
when we get there.

315
00:18:34,750 --> 00:18:37,586
Hell, I don't even know what I'm saying
anymore, and I don't really care!

316
00:18:37,795 --> 00:18:43,217
Sakura TV's ratings are gonna rocket
to 100, no, 120 percent for this special!

317
00:18:43,342 --> 00:18:45,010
[laughs maniacally]

318
00:18:45,511 --> 00:18:50,432
Come on, everyone! The new age
of Kira is about to arrive! [laughs]

319
00:18:58,899 --> 00:19:01,193
[Aizawa] The previous L
was suspicious of Light.

320
00:19:01,527 --> 00:19:05,447
But if Light is Kira, and I just come out
and say we should investigate him again,

321
00:19:05,614 --> 00:19:09,201
I'll probably end up dead just like L,
and that won't solve anything.

322
00:19:09,785 --> 00:19:12,162
The 13-day rule, huh?

323
00:19:13,330 --> 00:19:14,665
-[Ide] Aizawa.
-Huh?

324
00:19:15,082 --> 00:19:18,752
We have a long history. I can tell exactly
what you're thinking about,

325
00:19:18,836 --> 00:19:20,129
and what's bothering you.

326
00:19:20,462 --> 00:19:23,215
Between you and me, you should go ahead
and do what you think is right.

327
00:19:23,882 --> 00:19:27,052
I didn't trust L to begin with.
I never did, to be honest.

328
00:19:27,302 --> 00:19:29,471
I didn't sign up
to join the Kira task force

329
00:19:29,596 --> 00:19:30,848
because Light was running it.

330
00:19:30,973 --> 00:19:33,100
I joined because I wanted
to work with you.

331
00:19:33,350 --> 00:19:34,268
Ide…

332
00:19:35,060 --> 00:19:39,148
[Aizawa] Alright. I'll see if I can
contact Near without letting Light know.

333
00:19:39,690 --> 00:19:40,566
[Ide] Okay.

334
00:19:40,649 --> 00:19:43,610
I'll make sure that no one knows
what you're doing. You can count on me.

335
00:19:48,365 --> 00:19:49,491
[both cough awkwardly]

336
00:19:56,123 --> 00:19:57,124
[Aizawa] Hmm...

337
00:20:04,381 --> 00:20:09,428
Light, I really want to believe
that you're not Kira.

338
00:20:11,472 --> 00:20:13,056
Hmm...

339
00:20:13,766 --> 00:20:17,561
[panting] This is really bad!
Turn on the TV! It's Demegawa.

340
00:20:17,686 --> 00:20:19,396
-[all] Huh?
-[helicopter propeller thrumming]

341
00:20:21,023 --> 00:20:24,151
This is Demegawa, live.
My comrades and I

342
00:20:24,234 --> 00:20:26,820
have finally pinpointed the hideout
of the evil organization

343
00:20:26,945 --> 00:20:29,531
bent on trying to catch
our beloved god, Kira.

344
00:20:29,615 --> 00:20:31,533
We now have the building
completely surrounded!

345
00:20:31,700 --> 00:20:33,911
-[mob yelling]
-[man] Come on out!

346
00:20:34,161 --> 00:20:35,412
[man] Break down the door!

347
00:20:36,455 --> 00:20:39,458
[Demegawa] Right now, our enemies
appear to be hiding within the building.

348
00:20:39,541 --> 00:20:41,376
But they won't be able to hide
from us for long!

349
00:20:41,502 --> 00:20:42,419
[mob yelling]

350
00:20:42,503 --> 00:20:45,839
[Demegawa] Behold the power of the people!
The power of justice!

351
00:20:49,051 --> 00:20:52,471
[Misa] As soon as Near escapes,
I'm gonna write his name in the notebook.

352
00:20:52,638 --> 00:20:54,890
Don't worry, Light. I won't let you down.

353
00:20:55,724 --> 00:20:58,977
[Rester] At this rate, we'll be dragged
outside unless we stop them somehow.

354
00:20:59,061 --> 00:21:00,604
[monitors beeping]

355
00:21:01,855 --> 00:21:02,731
[Near] L…

356
00:21:03,148 --> 00:21:04,441
What's going on, Near?

357
00:21:05,317 --> 00:21:08,737
Could it be that this is some sort of plot
by Mello to finish off the SPK?

358
00:21:08,987 --> 00:21:12,115
No. Surely it couldn't be
that the SPK's security

359
00:21:12,199 --> 00:21:15,244
was so lax that even a normal citizen
could find out where it was located?

360
00:21:15,786 --> 00:21:17,037
[figurine snaps]

361
00:21:17,162 --> 00:21:19,915
[Near] Damn it.
He's lying through his teeth.

362
00:21:20,624 --> 00:21:24,169
[Light chuckling] I win, Near.

363
00:21:26,410 --> 00:21:33,334
TO BE CONTINUED

364
00:21:35,368 --> 00:21:38,195
[theme music playing]
